JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 53
IS  - 1
SP  - 113
EP  - 124
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper brings some empirical evidence to the construction of a more disaggregated view of disequilibrium. Individual data on firms collected by INSEE through periodic Business Surveys are used to construct the distribution of firms over the four possible disequilibrium regimes. Then the behavior of this distribution over time is analyzed by estimating dynamic conditional logit models on panel data.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297595
