T1  - Entry Deterrence and the Free Rider Problem
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297592
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 53
IS  - 1
SP  - 71
EP  - 83
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The public good aspect of entry prevention is examined in an industry characterized by an established oligopoly facing a potential entrant. Although incumbent firms act noncooperatively, underinvestment in entry-deterrence does not occur and in fact incumbents may find themselves in a Pareto dominated arrangement (in terms of profits) by preventing entry.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297592
